&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company Overview:&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Dialectic is a crypto-native firm of builders and capital advisors focused on investing in and building software across emerging crypto and blockchain technologies. We advise multiple liquid crypto funds specializing in DeFi yield strategies, run venture activity in the crypto/blockchain space, and steward 1OF1, a prominent digital art collection. We produce outlier results through diversified investment strategies across the decentralized finance ecosystem.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;We are looking for a Blockchain Developer to join our team full-time. The role is focused on blockchain applications — building backend tooling, connectors to on-chain systems, and data pipelines that feed our DeFi yield strategies and inform capital deployment decisions. You will be part of a small, dynamic team with real influence over technical decisions and direction.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and Maintain Backend Tooling and Services in Rust&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with the Yielding and Quant team to develop strategies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Optimize for low latency and inclusion of high throughput EVM transactions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the team with insights and best practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3 years professional software development experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2 years professional Rust experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1-2 years of experience in the Ethereum ecosystem&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with EVM and Solidity smart contracts is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with Rust Ethereum libraries (alloy, foundry)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Entrepreneurial, self motivated and driven&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong work ethic and team player&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Based in Swizterland and able to work from our office in Zug full time&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Dialectic offers an exceptional work culture:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dynamic and collegiality in a small team working in fields that are shaping the future of our society&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;As a modern employer, we offer you contemporary working conditions, a lot of space to develop yourself alongside the company as well as exciting and challenging projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Compelling compensation, bonus and participation opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to extremely talented people and very interesting clients who have unique investment profiles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supportive work and team atmosphere with flat hierarchies and a strong entrepreneurial spirit.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dialectic is an equal opportunity employer with strong diversity of ideas.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company Overview:&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Dialectic, a crypto-native organization of builders and capital advisors, is seeking a Developer to join the team on a full-time basis. This is a great opportunity to join a dynamic and fast-growing team, focused on investing in and building compelling software in emerging crypto and blockchain technologies. We produce outlier results through a series of diversified investment strategies in the decentralized finance ecosystem.&lt;/p&gt;
